## Down AKA Kilo

### Background Information

Born Juan Jose Martinez in the year 1985, he’s now hovering somewhere between thirty-nine and forty, a fact that seems to mildly inconvenience him. His origins trace back to [Oxnard, California](/Oxnard,_California), a place that apparently left its mark. His parents, immigrants from Mexico, brought him into a world that he’d later soundtrack with [hip hop](/hip_hop_music).

Martinez’s formative years were steeped in the sounds of [Cypress Hill](/Cypress_Hill) and the unapologetic narratives of [N.W.A](/N.W.A). By thirteen, the rhythm had taken hold, and he was already trying his hand at rapping. His early experiments weren’t in some sterile studio; they were in the garage of a childhood friend, Edward "E-Dub" Rios. This same Rios would later become a producer for [Power 106](/KPWR), specifically for the show "[Pocos Pero Locos](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pocos_Pero_Locos)". It’s a small detail, but tells you something about the ecosystem of ambition and sound he emerged from.

His career officially launched with his debut album, [California Cowboyz](/California_Cowboyz), in 2003. This was followed by [Definition of an Ese](/Definition_of_an_Ese) in 2007. The latter spawned two singles that managed to claw their way into public consciousness: "[Lean like a Cholo](/Lean_like_a_Cholo)" and the title track, "Definition of an Ese." These weren't just songs; they were snapshots of a particular culture, delivered with a cadence that resonated.

Life, however, has a way of interrupting even the most carefully crafted narratives. On March 28, 2009, Martinez was involved in a serious car crash in [Farmington, New Mexico](/Farmington,_New_Mexico). The incident left him in a coma, a stark reminder of the fragility that underlies even the most vibrant lives. He’s an artist who’s lived through more than just studio sessions and chart positions.

